{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a51a7a37c07b9faa2","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Use WebSearch and WebFetch to research the CONCRETE RESULTS on GOOGLE INFRASTRUCTURE / HARDWARE achieved by Google DeepMind's AlphaEvolve (2025). I need specific numbers with exact source URLs.\n\nFocus on these specific claims and verify exact figures:\n- Recovering 0.7% of Google's worldwide datacenter compute resources via a scheduling heuristic for Borg (Google's cluster management system), and that it has been in production for over a year\n- TPU circuit / arithmetic design improvements (e.g. removing/simplifying unnecessary bits in a Verilog/RTL arithmetic circuit, proposed for an upcoming TPU)\n- Gemini training kernel speedups (e.g. optimizing matrix multiplication / tiling heuristics in Pallas kernels, ~23% kernel speedup leading to ~1% reduction in Gemini's overall training time)\n- FlashAttention kernel optimization in the compiler (e.g. up to 32% speedup of the FlashAttention kernel implementation)\n\nPrefer primary sources: deepmind.google blog post (\"AlphaEvolve a Gemini-powered coding agent for designing advanced algorithms\"), the arxiv/DeepMind white paper PDF. Cross-check numbers.\n\nReturn a list of falsifiable, specific claims with exact numbers. Each claim MUST have its exact source URL. Quote DeepMind's wording where possible. Do not write files — return findings as your final text message."},"uuid":"0e84c21d-1a72-495a-a84b-5d48ccd57efb","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:46.496Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
