 vs. Human Ingenuity: Who Writes the Future of Code?\",\"url\":\"https://theaitrack.com/alphaevolve-ai-invents-better-algorithms/\"},{\"title\":\"DeepMind’s AlphaEvolve uses Gemini to optimise its own infrastructure and rediscover mathematics – Startup Fortune\",\"url\":\"https://startupfortune.com/deepminds-alphaevolve-uses-gemini-to-optimise-its-own-infrastructure-and-rediscover-mathematics/\"},{\"title\":\"AlphaEvolve: A Gemini-powered coding agent for designing advanced algorithms — Google DeepMind\",\"url\":\"https://deepmind.google/blog/alphaevolve-a-gemini-powered-coding-agent-for-designing-advanced-algorithms/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about AlphaEvolve:\n\n## AlphaEvolve Overview\n\nAlphaEvolve is an evolutionary coding agent powered by large language models for general-purpose algorithm discovery and optimization, pairing the creative problem-solving capabilities of Gemini models with automated evaluators that verify answers.\n\n## Key Performance Results\n\n**Gemini Kernel Optimization:**\nAlphaEvolve evolved a tiling heuristic that yielded a 23% average speedup on a critical kernel, leading to a 1% reduction in Gemini's overall training time.\n\n**TPU Verilog Circuit Design:**\nAlphaEvolve was tasked with optimizing the Verilog (hardware description language) code for an arithmetic circuit in a TPU. AlphaEvolve proposed a Verilog rewrite that removed unnecessary bits in a key, highly optimized arithmetic circuit for matrix multiplication.\n\n**FlashAttention Optimization:**\nBy modifying compiler-generated IR code, AlphaEvolve achieved a 32% kernel and 15% pre/post speedup for FlashAttention.\n\nThese optimizations demonstrate AlphaEvolve's ability to improve hardware design, AI training efficiency, and compiler-level code across multiple domains.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"e458d97f-c943-493c-b6e8-424d0b8f09f7","timestamp":"2026-06-21T